This article is a Presidential Memorandum issued by Barack Obama in February 2012. The memo discusses the need for the Federal Government to allocate resources effectively in order to support American competitiveness, innovation, and job growth. It highlights the importance of increasing exports and attracting foreign investment to create good, high-paying jobs. The memo mentions the National Export Initiative and the Export Promotion Cabinet, which work to improve conditions for exporting and doubling exports by the end of 2014. It also discusses the proposal to create a new department to streamline trade functions and promote competitiveness. The memo directs the Export Promotion Cabinet to develop strategies and initiatives in support of trade and investment goals, improve customer service for exporters, evaluate resource allocation, coordinate offices and staff, and enhance business competitiveness. The memo concludes with general provisions regarding implementation and legal considerations.